  <h4>protected areas</h4> 
	
	<p>Protected areas data are provided from the World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA); the most comprehensive global spatial dataset on terrestrial and marine protected areas. The WDPA is a joint project of UNEP and IUCN, produced by UNEP-WCMC and the IUCN World Commission on Protected Areas (WCPA), and contains information from national governments, non-governmental organizations, academic institutions, international biodiversity convention secretariats and many others. As of October 2010, the WDPA is openly available on its interactive host website, <a href="http://protectedplanet.org">protected planet</a></p>

  <h4 id="kbas">key biodiversity areas</h4>
	<p>Key Biodiversity Areas represent sites identified as the most important areas for biodiversity conservation worldwide. They are identified using a simple globally standardised criteria based on importance in maintaining species populations.</p>
