  <h4 id="fstat">forest status</h4>
  <p>The different classes of forest degradation were derived by comparing spatial data on the potential extent of forest with spatial data on the current extent of forest. Potential extent was generated from existing ecoregion/ecozone classifications (FAO, 1999, Olson et al., 2001) and climate data (Hijmans et al., 2005). A global forest map (SDSU 2011) was used to map the current extent of forests and a tree canopy density map (Hansen et al 2003) was used to separate them into open and closed forests within their common extent and to add woodlands areas. </p>
	<p>It is important to note, that the map of potential forest extent is valid at the macro-regional level only and might be inaccurate at the local level (for further information see (WRI 2011)). </p>
