  <h4 id="carbon_potential">carbon sequestration potential</h4>
	<p>Potential maximum carbon stock was mapped using the data from Ruesch and Gibbs (2008), including any relevant adjustments or additions that have been incorporated in the UNEP-WCMC Carbon and Biodiversity Calculator. The difference between the potential maximum carbon stock and the current carbon stock was calculated through geospatial analysis. This dataset builds on the assumption that restoration will not change the carbon content of the soil, which in the long term is unlikely.</p>
	<p>The assessment gives a coarse and highly uncertain, but spatially explicit, estimate of the amount of carbon that could potentially be gained through restoration of opportunity areas up to the level of carbon stocking that is represented by comparable non-degraded areas. The dataset was generated at 1km cell resolution. For further information see WRI (2011).</p>
