  <h6>Ecuador</h6>
	<p>Ecuador has identified terrestrial and marine Conservation Priority Areas and ‘ecological gaps’ in the national protected areas system. These are areas of importance for conservation of key species and/or ecosystems, and mostly are not yet designated as Protected Areas. The criteria used to identify the sites include occurrence of particular species and habitat types, as well as irreplaceability of sites and their vulnerability to pressures that affect biodiversity (Cuesta et al. 2006; Campos et al. 2007). Areas were classified into six categories of conservation priority.</p>
