	<p>Peru has identified 133 priority areas for conservation which represent sites that are nationally unique.  At the finer regional scale, 90 priority areas are also identified and mapped.  Please note that not all regions have to date submitted their prioritization data to SERNANP, and so at the regional scale the list of priority areas is incomplete.  Further information on priorities can be found in:</p>
