	<h6>The Bahamas</h6>
	<p>The Bahamas has identified marine and terrestrial conservation priority areas and ecological gaps in the national protected areas system in their first Ecological Gap Assessment in 2007.  These are areas of importance for conservation of key species and/or ecosystems which are not yet designated as Protected Areas.  Please note that a degree of priority was not assigned to each of these areas.  Please also be advised that the BEST Commission are presently engaged in a review process of that assessment to reflect priorities as part of the GEF Full Size Project which is expected to be finalized in February 2014.    Background information on the first Gap Assessment can be found in:</p>
